many checks lately.

204
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:15,847
Thanks for your help.

205
00:09:15,847 --> 00:09:18,767
So, how much?

206
00:09:18,767 --> 00:09:21,019
A hundred thousand
before sales tax.

207
00:09:21,019 --> 00:09:23,521
Huh?

208
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:25,440
Having a fire sale?

209
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:30,528
There.

210
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:32,447
Hmm, there's just
a little matter

211
00:09:32,447 --> 00:09:34,699
of a missing zero
on this check, ma'am.

212
00:09:34,699 --> 00:09:36,201
What?

213
00:09:36,201 --> 00:09:37,869
It can be difficult
writing checks

214
00:09:37,869 --> 00:09:39,662
when you're not used to it.

215
00:09:39,662 --> 00:09:40,872
It's nothing
to be ashamed of,

216
00:09:40,872 --> 00:09:43,917
it happens with
lower‐end clients like you.

217
00:09:43,917 --> 00:09:45,794
Frightfully careless of me.

218
00:09:45,794 --> 00:09:48,338
You certainly earned
your salary today.

219
00:10:03,061 --> 00:10:04,187
Whoa!

220
00:10:04,187 --> 00:10:06,147
Hey!

221
00:10:06,147 --> 00:10:09,150
That's it, show that
swordfish who's boss, man.

222
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:11,569
(grunting)

223
00:10:11,569 --> 00:10:13,446
(water splashing)

224
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:20,745
(yelps)

225
00:10:20,745 --> 00:10:22,372
I was so close.

226
00:10:22,372 --> 00:10:24,207
Step aside, sonny boy.

227
00:10:24,207 --> 00:10:25,333
Here.

228
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,293
Now, watch and learn, fellas.

229
00:10:29,337 --> 00:10:31,005
Excuse me for
interrupting you, gramps,

230
00:10:31,005 --> 00:10:33,091
but that thing doesn't
seem to have any line on it.

231
00:10:33,091 --> 00:10:36,553
Now, you see a plain old line
is just gonna break on me.

232
00:10:36,553 --> 00:10:37,887
Can't argue with that.

233
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:39,973
But how are you gonna
catch any fish?

234
00:10:39,973 --> 00:10:41,474
An electronic device.

235
00:10:41,474 --> 00:10:43,726
It disables the critter
so I can just pluck him

236
00:10:43,726 --> 00:10:45,436
out of the water
when I feel like it.

237
00:10:45,436 --> 00:10:47,272
Electronic, huh?

238
00:10:47,272 --> 00:10:49,983
Mm‐hmm.

239
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:52,277
I think up ideas
all the time.

240
00:10:52,277 --> 00:10:53,444
The name's Jebopee.

241
00:10:53,444 --> 00:10:54,946
You probably know
some of my stuff.

242
00:10:54,946 --> 00:10:56,990
Yeah, for instance,
this little light saber

243
00:10:56,990 --> 00:10:58,825
thing‐a‐majig works too.

244
00:10:58,825 --> 00:11:00,118
‐Look!
‐Huh?

245
00:11:00,118 --> 00:11:01,369
‐Huh?
‐Huh?

246
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:02,328
Huh?

247
00:11:04,789 --> 00:11:06,708
It's a shame, never did
get a patent for this

248
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:09,127
thing‐a‐mabob, and that's
why I'm still so poor.

249
00:11:09,127 --> 00:11:10,628
That's how it goes, I guess.

250
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:12,547
(chuckles)

251
00:11:12,547 --> 00:11:15,466
Yup, now just sit back
and marvel at the amazing

252
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:18,678
power of the Jebopee
light saber sport fisherman.

253
00:11:18,678 --> 00:11:20,221
♪

254
00:11:20,221 --> 00:11:22,056
Ah, there he is.

255
00:11:22,056 --> 00:11:23,933
(laser buzzing)

256
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:25,643
You see that?

257
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:27,937
Told you, like a charm!

258
00:11:27,937 --> 00:11:30,648
♪

259
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:32,233
(chuckles)

260
00:11:32,233 --> 00:11:35,028
This line won't ever break.

261
00:11:35,028 --> 00:11:38,114
(chuckles)

262
00:11:38,114 --> 00:11:39,157
Huh?

263
00:11:39,157 --> 00:11:40,283
Ah!

